item.description:
AN OUT OF THIS WORLD COMMUNITY
Not only is the Exeter UFO Festival an educational experience for both believers and skeptics alike, but it's a fun time for families and friends. In addition to the world premier of the documentary film From the Stars to New Hampshire: the Hill Abduction & the Exeter Encounter and an esteemed panel of experts, there will be activities for the kids and a self-guided UFO safari.

The 3rd annual Exeter UFO Festival begins at 8:30am and runs until 10pm.

All lectures and festival events are free of charge - no tickets needed!

 

The festival will take place in Downtown Exeter, New Hampshire
Lectures will be held at Exeter Town Hall: 10 Front St, Exeter, New Hampshire
Festival activities will be held outside of Town Hall and in Founders Park.

For more information visit... www.exeterufofestival.com
